SUMMARY:LATEX. // HADAL ZONE // TORONTO
DESCRIPTION:Saturday\, April 11\, 2025  // 10pm\n$30 – $45 + fees\nBUY TICKETS \n \nOn April 11th\, we descend into the HADAL ZONE\, where no sunlight reaches and only the adaptable survive. On this night\, the surface is irrelevant. \nExpect abyssal sub-bass\, slow-burning deep-sea techno\, and performances that feel less like spectacle and more like transformation. At Buddies\, the room compresses. The air thickens. The dance floor mutates. \nTension. Compression. Release. \nLeave your problems at the shoreline. \nWe’re diving deeper. \n\n  \nDJ’s \nGRRLCRRSH https://www.instagram.com/grrlcrrsh/ \nR-ODERICK https://www.instagram.com/r_od3rick/ \nCRISSEMARQUEUR https://www.instagram.com/crissemarqueur/ \n  \nPerformances \nKira https://www.instagram.com/ohitskayinn/ \nFyu Sha https://www.instagram.com/fyu.sha/ \nGushy https://www.instagram.com/gushy.irl/ \nSaint https://www.instagram.com/saint.spins/ \nFaith x Kiwi https://www.instagram.com/faith.alexandra.marie/ x https://www.instagram.com/kiwithestripp3r/ \nN9ne https://www.instagram.com/n9neinthehouse/ \n  \nDungeon Monitor \nThe Goddess Phoenix https://www.instagram.com/goddess_nymphoenixx \n  \nPhotography \nJesus ‘ Sister https://www.instagram.com/jesusssister \n  \n————————————————————————————————————————————— \n  \n  \nGROUND RULES\nIn case of infringement\, refunds will not be provided \n//DRESS CODE// \n  \nLatex is a kink event and we simply do not want people showing up with just jeans and a T-shirt. \nThe outfit is absolutely mandatory and if you don’t feel comfortable around kink\, nudity or BDSM practices LATEX might not be the appropriate event for you. \nWe strongly encourage kink wear // LATEX / PVC / LEATHER / CHAINS / LINGERIE etc… \nIf you have any doubts\, feel free to contact us. \n  \n//CONSENT// \n  \nWhen meeting someone new\, please ask for their pronouns! It doesn’t feel nice to be misgendered. \nASK FOR CONSENT! If not you will be asked to leave. \n– Please make sure you approach the people you are interested in face to face\, and not from the side or from behind. \n– Look for an enthusiastic yes! \n– Remember that people can change their minds or modify their consent at any time. \nWe will have designated people you can go to in case anything happens. (Pink armbands) \n  \nYou are responsible for the attitude of the people you invite to our events and you can be held accountable for their misbehavior. Please choose wisely who you bring with you in order to keep LATEX a safe space for everyone. \n  \n//PERFORMERS// \n  \nPLEASE DO NOT BOTHER OR INTERACT WITH THE PERFORMERS DURING THEIR PURRRFORMANCES. \nFeel free to tip your favorite. \n  \n//THE NO NO NO’s// \n  \nZero tolerance for verbal or physical harassment\, racism\, xenophobia\, sexism\, transphobia\, homophobia etc. \nNO photos/videos or cellphone use inside the venue. A designated professional photographer will be covering the event. \nNO BYOB \nNO smoking inside \nNO leering\, creeping\, following\, or insisting. \nDefinition of leering: looking or gazing in a lascivious or unpleasant way. \n  \nDUNGEON RULES \n  \n// RESPECT THE PEOPLE // \na. Consent is mandatory – if it’s not an enthusiastic yes\, it’s a no! \nb. No interrupting a scene! \nc. Dungeon Monitors wearing pink armbands are here to help you \nd. RED always means stop! \n  \n// RESPECT THE SPACE! // \na. Use furniture and toys as intended \nb. Make sure you have enough space to play safely \nc. Don’t hog the furniture \nIf you infringe any of these rules\, we will ask you to leave the dungeon and won’t be granted access back. \n  \nRespect\, consent\, and care guide everything here. \nThis is a space to explore safely remember to dress for the vibe (latex\, leather\, fetish\, or other expressive attire encouraged)\, respect boundaries\, and look out for one another. \nNo phones. No judgment. \nJust being fully present together. \n  \nProduced by \nSlata Productions
URL:https://buddiesinbadtimes.com/event/latex-hadal-zone-toronto/
LOCATION:Tallulahs
END:VEVENT
